{"key":"processedPost-10463864","value":{"id":10463864,"first":10463805,"last":10463925,"when":1244352182,"utime":"06/07/09 08:23 AM","content":"A good perlite rinse never hurts.&nbsp; When it gets dirty, you can boil it in a large kettle of water, rinse and re-use.&nbsp; It never rots or molds, but it does get dirty when stuff spills into it.<br />It also helps between flushes to rake the perlite with your fingers to fluff it back up.&nbsp; Packed perlite doesn't work well.&nbsp; You want it loose and airy.&nbsp; I like to make little mountains and valleys, because it increases the surface area, thus giving better humidity.<br />RR","title":"Re: Resoaking pearlite"}}